name: Brownie Batter Dip (aka Chocolate Hummus)
author: ConnorsMom
summary: At first I was skeptical of 'dessert' hummus. Then I tried some. I was hooked. It is awesome on apples, strawberries, pretzels and lots of other things.
ingredients: 1 (15 ounce) can chickpeas (garbanzo beans), rinsed and drained
½ cup unsweetened dark cocoa powder
3 tablespoons water, or more if needed
directions: Combine chickpeas, cocoa powder, sugar, olive oil, peanut butter, vanilla extract, and salt in a food processor; blend, scraping down sides as needed, until smooth
Begin adding water while processor is running and blend until desired consistency is reached
